        "parent": "t-overview-0",
        "title": "Charter Rights & Freedoms"
      },
      {
        "id": "t-overview-0-s-2-f-0",
        "parent": "t-overview-0-s-2",
        "title": "Charter Rights & Freedoms are fundamental principles enshrined in the Canadian Constitution."
      },
      {
        "id": "t-overview-0-s-2-f-1",
        "parent": "t-overview-0-s-2",
        "title": "These rights protect individual freedoms and often conflict with provincial jurisdiction, leading to a complex legal framework."
      },
      {
        "id": "t-overview-0-s-2-f-2",
        "parent": "t-overview-0-s-2",
        "title": "The division of power between federal and provincial governments creates overlapping jurisdictions for various legal issues."
